[2]
Date: Wed 29 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: EU, DG Health & Consumer Protection website [edited]
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/adns/table_11_2006/adns_241106_en.pdf>


EU Animal disease notification system (ADNS)
-----------------------------------------------
According to the most current weekly update of table 11 (animal
disease situation per country and per disease, distributed 27 Nov
2006), the total number of confirmed bluetongue outbreaks, reported
by European Union member states during the period 1 Jan 2006 to 24
Nov 2006, was 2057 (178 added during the week of 17 to 24 Nov 2006,
compared to 197 added during the week of 10-17 Nov and 207 during the
week of 3-10 Nov 2006).

The following summarized, confirmed 2006 outbreaks are retrieved from
the last (24 Nov 2006) and the 4 previous weekly ADNS reports:

Country / 24 Nov / 17 Nov / 10 Nov / 3 Nov / 27 Oct / last confirmation date

1. Belgium / 670 / 626 / 590 / 490 / 460 / 22 Nov 2006
2. Germany / 812 / 744 / 630 / 592 / 472 / 22 Nov 2006
3. France / 6 / 6 / 5 / 5 / 5 / 14 Nov 2006
4. Netherlands / 445 / 437 / 409 / 359 / 317 / 23 Nov 2006
5. Bulgaria / 13 / 13 / 13 / 8 / 8 / 5 Nov 2006
6. Italy / 110 / 52 / 35 / 21 / 0 / 13 Nov 2006
7. Portugal / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 14 Nov 2006

--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The following data are related to the evolution of the BTV-8
epizootic in northwest Europe during the last 6 weeks.

Country: new outbreaks in weeks ending 20 Oct / 27 Oct / 3 Nov / 10
Nov / 17 Nov / 24 Nov 2006

Belgium: 106 / 57 / 30 / 100 / 36 / 44
Netherlands: 57 / 54 / 42 / 50 / 28 / 8
Germany: 157 / 107 / 120 / 38 / 114 / 68
France: 0 / 0 / 0 / 0 / 1 / 0

An updated map showing the BTV-8 outbreaks in the above countries
from 17 Aug to 24 Nov 2006 is available at
<http://www.defra.gov.uk/animalh/diseases/notifiable/pdf/bt-europemap.pdf>.

For further details and maps on the evolution of the BTV-8 epizootic,
see the 29 Nov 2006 update of "Bluetongue Serotype 8 Epidemic
Bulletin" by the EFSA Epidemiology Working Group at
<http://www.efsa.europa.eu/en/in_focus/bluetongue/outbreak_overview.html>.
- Mod.AS]

